<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871229-0056 </DOCNO><HL> Argo-Tech Gets Credit Line</HL><DD> 12/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Argo-Tech Corp. said it arranged a $75 million revolving credit line through an eight-bank syndicate managed by MNC Commercial Corp. of Baltimore.    Argo-Tech, formerly the power accessories division of TRW Inc., is a closely held maker of fuel pumps for jet aircraft, among other things. It had fiscal 1987 sales of more than $180 million.    The company said it will use the credit line for working capital and to expand plant capacity. </TEXT></DOC>